40. arguta, etc.: the two meth- ods of publication are referred to in chiastic order: first, comedy and tragedy for the theatre3 second, epic and bucolic poetry for recitation. — meretrice: in the abl. absolute with eludente, giving the subject of the writing through the charac- ters usually appearing in that form of composition. -— arguta, cunning. — meretrice, one of the most com· mon characters in the comedy.— Davo, a characteristic slave name. See Ter. Andria. — Chremeta, the

old man of the comedy. See Ter. Adelphi.

41. eludente: the tricks of the , slave, who assists his young master in. deceiving the father, form the staple of the new comedy. The meretrix also assisted in these.
